
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dehtmldiff` baraye moghayese va namayesh taghirat bein do ta file HTML estefade mishavad.  In dastoor taghirat ra be shekle HTML mark mikonad ta didane fargh-ha asan tar shavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--output-type=inline`  --> 📝 Taghirat ra dar haman file asli HTML mark mikonad.
    🔹 `--chars`  --> 🔡 Taghirat dar character level ra neshon midahad (bejoz kalame ya khat).
    🔹 `--words`  --> 🔑 Taghirat dar word level ra neshon midahad (default).
    🔹 `--split`  --> ✂️ Namayesh taghirat dar do stolon joda baraye behtar didane fargh-ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dehtmldiff file1.html file2.html > diff.html

    🔹 In dastoor file1.html va file2.html ra moghayese mikonad va natije ra dar file diff.html zakhire mikonad.

    $ dehtmldiff --output-type=inline file1.html file2.html

    🔹 In dastoor taghirat ra dar file1.html mark mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dehtmldiff old.html new.html

    🔹 HTML diff bein `old.html` va `new.html` ra dar terminal namayesh midahad. Shoma mitavanid in ra redirect konid be yek file HTML digar (`> diff.html`) baraye didane behtar dar browser.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dehtmldiff` command is used to compare and display the differences between two HTML files. It marks the changes in HTML format, making it easier to see the differences.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--output-type=inline`  --> 📝 Marks the changes directly in the original HTML file.
    🔹 `--chars`  --> 🔡 Shows changes at the character level (instead of word or line).
    🔹 `--words`  --> 🔑 Shows changes at the word level (default).
    🔹 `--split`  --> ✂️ Displays changes in two separate columns for better comparison.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dehtmldiff file1.html file2.html > diff.html

    🔹 This command compares file1.html and file2.html and saves the result in the diff.html file.

    $ dehtmldiff --output-type=inline file1.html file2.html

    🔹 This command marks the changes directly in the file1.html.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dehtmldiff old.html new.html

    🔹 Displays the HTML diff between `old.html` and `new.html` in the terminal. You can redirect this to another HTML file (`> diff.html`) for easier viewing in a browser.
